When Ohio Gov. John Kasich took office he promised to bring Ohio&rsquo;s budget back in the black. He kept good on that promise as the state ended the first half of the two-year budget with an $800 million surplus. Republicans quickly stashed that money aside, however, to cover the acceleration of the personal income tax in last year&rsquo;s budget, according to WVXU.
